properties.name: House 1
properties.description: Posted by Akg * Completion Jan 2007 Only * Beutifully Presented * Two Reception Rooms * Lovely Kitchen/breakfast * Four Bedrooms * Two Bath/shower Rooms * Excellent Storage * South Facing Rear Garden Beautifully presented detached family home built only a few years ago and further improved by the Vendors who have owned it since new. Entrance hall, cloakroom, lounge with stone gas flame fireplace, dining room, lovely kitchen/breakfast room and utility room downstairs. Main bedroom with lots of good quality built-in wardrobes and en-suite shower room, three further bedrooms - all with good quality and ample built-in wardrobes, family bathroom. A special feature is the lovely South facing landscaped rear garden and patio. Single integral garage. Viewings recommended. Upward chain complete - quick exchange with completion January 2007.

properties.name: House 2
properties.description: Posted by Akg * Private Rear Garden * 2 Reception Rooms * Stunning Conservatory * Kitchen/breakfast Room * Four Double Bedrooms * Two Bath/shower Rooms * Converted Single Garage * Garden Backs Onto Woods Beautifully presented detached family home in the popular Greenham design in what is arguably one of the best roads in Dunston Park and backing onto woodland, this must be seen! Entrance hall, cloakroom, good sized lounge, dining room, stunning conservatory, kitchen/breakfast room, utility room, large double bedroom with en-suite shower room, three further double bedrooms, family bathroom. The single garage has been partially converted into a study but this could easily be changed back. Very private rear garden backing onto woodland. Viewings strongly recommended.

properties.name: House 3
properties.description: Posted by Akg * Kennet School Catchment * Quiet Cul-de-sac * Three Reception Rooms * Refitted Kitchen/b\'fast * Utility & Cloakroom * Four Bedrooms * Two Bathrooms * Double Garage Imposing residence in a quiet cul-de-sac location in what is arguably one of the best roads in Dunston Park and benefitting from being in the Kennet School catchment area. Entrance hall, cloakroom, study/family room, living room, dining room, re-fitted kitchen/breakfast room, utility room, main bedroom with en-suite shower room, three further bedrooms, family bathroom. Fully enclosed rear garden. Double garage plus driveway parking. Viewings strongly recommended.

properties.name: House 4
properties.description: Posted by Akg * Two Gardens! * Further Potential * Three Reception Rooms * Kitchen/breakfast Room * Four Double Bedrooms * Two Bath/shower Rooms * Extra Long Tandem Garage * No Onward Chain Handsome family home with two gardens and lots of further potential! Only two houses in this design were built in Dunston Park - this light and spacious detached property is uniquely located on a corner plot and therefore sits in an above average sized plot, with a good degree of privacy, and gardens on two sides. The house lends itself to further extension, particularly in the enormous loft space (subject to Planning Permissions). Entrance hall, cloakroom, study/family room, lounge, dining room, kitchen/breakfast room, utility room, four double bedrooms, two bath/shower rooms. Extra long tandem garage plus further parking. No onward chain. We highly recommend a full inspection of this unusual and special property!

properties.name: House 6
properties.description: Posted by Akg * Desirable Property * Excellent School Location * Well Presented * 4 Bedrooms * En-suite * Gas Central Heating * Double Garage * Landscaped Garden AN OPPORTUNITY NOT TO BE MISSED. A most desirable property situated in this popular residential area South of Newbury and within the catchment area of Park House, St. Bart\'s and Falkland Primary School. Comprising large entrance hall, L-Shaped sitting / dining room, kitchen / breakfast room and cloakroom. Master bedroom with en-suite. Three further bedrooms and family bathroom. Benefits include UPVC double glazing, gas central heating, double garage and attractive landscaped terraced gardens.

properties.name: House 7
properties.description: Posted by AkgFamily living in Hermitage! This four bedroomed detached property is well located in this excellent village with several pubs, post office/stores and church all wtihin a short walk away. The village also provides excellent access onto A34/M4 (J13) and is renowned for its good schools including The Downs School. Entrance hall, cloakroom, lounge with fireplace, conservatory, dining room, re-fitted kitchen/breakfast room, utility room, main bedroom with en-suite shower room, three further bedroms, family bathroom. Double garage plus driveway parking. Enclosed rear garden. Viewings recommended.

properties.name: House 8
properties.description: Posted by AkgAn opportunity to purchase a deceptively spacious detached house, placed on the highly-regarded and popular Manor Fields development on the edge of the town. The accommodation benefits from a skillful loft conversion (providing two extra bedrooms and a shower room) as well as a conservatory, a re-fitted en-suite shower and family bathroom. There is a double garage, driveway parking and a private rear garden. This property has to be viewed internally to be appreciated, which we highly recommend. Briefly the accommodation comprises: Five Bedrooms * Re-Fitted En-Suite Shower Room * Sitting Room * Dining Room * Conservatory * Kitchen/Breakfast Room * Utility Room * Cloakroom * Re-Fitted Bathroom * Enclosed Storm Porch & Hall * Double-Glazing * Gas Central Heating * Double Garage * Driveway Parking * Enclosed Rear Gardens

properties.name: House 9
properties.description: Posted by AkgA four bedroom detached house situated on the edge of this well regarded village incorporating cloakroom, two receptions, spacious kitchen/breakfast room, en-suite bathroom to the master bedroom and benefiting from larger than average gardens, double garage, gas central heating to radiators and double glazed windows.
